<text>Potential cut-off


Truncation of a potential function that would otherwise go to infinity. Only the forces arising from the atoms that fall into the cut-off sphere are calculated. Without a smoothing function, this can lead to a computational violation of energy conservation law for isolated systems, and sometimes a numerical instability. 


 
